---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TimeLineElement from "../components/cv/TimeLine.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" sideBarActiveItemID="cv">
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">About</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-10 text-justify">
    Quantitative researcher and machine learning practitioner with a focus on financial markets.
    I write about the practical application of statistical models, deep learning architectures
    and optimisation techniques to problems in asset management, risk and algorithmic trading.
    My work sits at the intersection of rigorous mathematical finance and modern data science,
    with an emphasis on reproducibility and production-ready implementations in Python.
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Education</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container grid gap-4 mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="MSc Financial Engineering"
      subtitle="2016 to 2018 at Universidad Politécnica de Madrid, Madrid, Spain"
    />
    <TimeLineElement
      title="BSc Mathematics & Statistics"
      subtitle="2012 to 2016 at Universidad Autónoma de Madrid, Madrid, Spain"
    />
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Experience</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Senior Quantitative Researcher"
      subtitle="From 2022 to Present at Pantagruel Capital, Madrid, Spain"
    >
      Leading quantitative research initiatives in systematic equity strategies. Development of machine learning models for alpha generation,
      portfolio construction and execution cost modelling. Research on alternative data integration and NLP pipelines for earnings call analysis.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Quantitative Analyst"
      subtitle="From 2019 to 2022 at Algorithmia AM, London, UK"
    >
      Built and maintained factor models and risk engines for a multi-asset portfolio. Implemented deep learning forecasting models
      for volatility and cross-sectional return prediction. Backtesting infrastructure development in Python and C++.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Data Scientist – Financial Markets"
      subtitle="From 2018 to 2019 at BBVA Data & Analytics, Madrid, Spain"
    >
      Developed credit risk scoring models using gradient boosting and logistic regression. Analysis of transactional data
      for retail banking clients and regulatory reporting (IFRS 9 / Basel III).
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Certifications</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc mx-6 mb-10 grid gap-2">
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.cfainstitute.org/" target="_blank">CFA Level II Candidate – CFA Institute</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.tensorflow.org/certificate" target="_blank">TensorFlow Developer Certificate – Google</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/certification/" target="_blank">AWS Certified Machine Learning – Specialty</a>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Skills</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc md:columns-5 columns-2 mx-6">
    <li>Python</li>
    <li>PyTorch</li>
    <li>TensorFlow</li>
    <li>scikit-learn</li>
    <li>Pandas / NumPy</li>
    <li>SQL</li>
    <li>R</li>
    <li>C++</li>
    <li>Time Series</li>
    <li>Portfolio Opt.</li>
    <li>Risk Modelling</li>
    <li>NLP</li>
    <li>Reinforcement RL</li>
    <li>Factor Models</li>
    <li>Docker / MLOps</li>
  </ul>
</BaseLayout>
